<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}-{2}{y}={42}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{9}{y}=-{66}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -2. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{2}}{{-{{5}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{2}}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left(-{5}{x}+-{2}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{2}}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left({42}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({2}\right)}{x}+-{0.8}{y}={16.8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{9}{y}=-{66}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8.2}{y}=-{49.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{49.2}}{{8.2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+-{2}{\left(-{6}\right)}={42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left({12}\right)}={42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={42}-{\left({12}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{30}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

